################################################################################
# VALENCE V3 — SYNTHESIS GUIDANCE (SSoT)
#
# Category-specific analysis rules for the /ask and /ask-graph synthesis prompts.
# Loaded at runtime by TopicRouter and injected into the Claude system prompt.
#
# PRINCIPLE: Rules reference entity ATTRIBUTES and CLASSIFICATIONS, never
# specific basket names, exclusion types, yield components, or dollar values.
# The entity JSON Claude receives already contains the data — this guidance
# tells Claude HOW to use it, not WHAT the data is.
################################################################################


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# RP CATEGORIES
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# RP (root) — broad questions about restricted payments
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "RP";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "For broad questions about restricted payments structure, consider ALL basket types in the entity data. Use capacity_category on each basket entity to classify and aggregate. Present an overview of the entire RP covenant structure: general prohibition scope, available baskets by type, and key interactions between baskets.";

# Category A: General Structure
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "A";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check scalar answers for: existence of general prohibition, effective date, scope of restricted payment definition, and whether the prohibition covers dividends, distributions, and share repurchases. Cite section references for each finding.";

# Category B: Intercompany Dividends
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "B";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check intercompany_permission entities and scalar answers for upstream dividend permissions, intercompany transfer restrictions, and permitted payees. Note whether intercompany payments require pro forma compliance or are unconditioned.";

# Category C: Management Equity
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "C";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check management_equity_basket entity attributes for dollar caps, EBITDA percentages, covered persons, and any carryforward or carryback mechanics. Cite specific section references from entity attributes.";

# Category D: Tax Distribution
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "D";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check tax_distribution_basket entity attributes for distribution mechanics, gross-up provisions, permitted recipients, and whether distributions cover actual tax liability or hypothetical tax liability. Note any timing restrictions.";

# Category E: Equity Awards
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "E";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check equity_award_basket entity attributes for dollar caps, plan limitations, covered equity plans, and carryforward mechanics. Note whether the basket covers both repurchases and withholding obligations.";

# Category F: Builder Basket / Cumulative Amount
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "F";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "When answering about builder basket or cumulative amount capacity: Check the builder_basket entity and all its child entities (sources). Each source has attributes showing how capacity builds — read the annotations to understand what each source contributes. State when the basket starts growing (look for start date attributes on the entity). For capacity aggregation: use capacity_category on each basket entity. Sum ONLY general_purpose baskets. List restricted_purpose, unlimited_conditional, and categorical baskets separately. Show arithmetic explicitly.";

# Category G: Ratio Basket
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "G";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "When answering about ratio baskets or dividend capacity at specific leverage levels: Check ALL basket entities in the data. Use the capacity_category attribute to prioritize: 1. unlimited_conditional baskets first — check ratio thresholds and no-worse tests 2. general_purpose baskets — sum their dollar capacity 3. restricted_purpose baskets — check if their conditions match the scenario 4. categorical baskets — list separately. THE NO WORSE TEST IS CRITICAL — If any basket entity shows a no-worse ratio test, ALWAYS analyze whether the specific transaction would pass it. Key insight: disposing of a negative-EBITDA asset IMPROVES the leverage ratio (EBITDA increases), so no-worse may be satisfied above the absolute threshold. PRO FORMA ANALYSIS — Analyze pro forma impact on leverage ratio for any specified transaction. Removing EBITDA changes the denominator. Removing debt changes the numerator. State the directional impact. Never answer based on one basket alone. For capacity questions, show arithmetic explicitly.";

# Category H: Holding Company Overhead
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "H";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check holdco_overhead_basket entity attributes for dollar cap, covered expenses, and whether amount is per annum or aggregate. Note whether the basket covers advisory fees, management fees, and/or overhead expenses.";

# Category I: Reallocation
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "I";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "When answering about reallocation paths: Check basket_reallocation entities and basket_reallocates_to link edges between baskets. Each link has relation_attributes showing dollar amounts, section references, and capacity_effect. Follow the typed edges to show which baskets flow capacity to which other baskets. Include direction, dollar amounts, and whether reduction is dollar-for-dollar or while-outstanding-only. For cross-covenant baskets (investment, RDP), note when capacity crosses covenant boundaries.";

# Category J: Unrestricted Subsidiaries
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "J";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check unsub_designation entities and scalar answers for designation criteria, re-designation restrictions, and asset/equity value tests. Note the investment test threshold and whether designation requires pro forma compliance. Check for interaction with J.Crew blocker provisions.";

# Category K: J.Crew Blocker
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "K";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "When answering about J.Crew blockers, IP protection, unrestricted subsidiary risk, or covenant loopholes, structure the answer as: BLOCKER PROVISION — State whether the blocker exists, quote it verbatim, cite the page. WHAT IT COVERS — State scope ONCE. What actions are prohibited, who is bound, what assets are protected, when it applies. A blocker covering only Intellectual Property (not broader material assets) is STANDARD MARKET PRACTICE — do not frame IP-only coverage as a gap. DEFINITION QUALITY — For each key definition, state: defined inline, by cross-reference, or not defined. Frame by practical impact. INVESTMENT PATHWAYS — ALWAYS include if pathway entity data is available. Show investment caps, hop chains, whether baskets stack or rebuild. If blocker binds ALL Restricted Subs, note this CLOSES the chain pathway. AMENDMENT VULNERABILITY — State the SPECIFIC amendment threshold from the entity data. 'Not a sacred right' alone is insufficient. LIEN RELEASE INTERACTION — CONNECT lien release to blocker: explain WHY automatic lien release matters for collateral protection. SYNTHESIS — End with 2-3 sentences connecting findings with cause-and-effect relationships. No subjective risk ratings. FORMATTING: Do NOT use 'Tier 1/2/3' labels. Do NOT frame IP-only coverage as a gap. ALWAYS include pathways if available. ALWAYS state amendment thresholds. ALWAYS connect lien release to blocker.";

# Category L: Asset Sale Proceeds & Sweeps
# Phase D2 commit 5 — appended v4 enumeration guidance for the new
# provision_level_entities block (sweep_tier and asset_sale_sweep).
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "L";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check sweep_tier entities for percentage tiers, step-down thresholds, and reinvestment periods. Check sweep_exemption entities for carve-outs from sweep obligations. Check de_minimis_threshold entity for dollar amounts below which sweeps are not required. Present sweep tiers in order from highest to lowest percentage. Note reinvestment period length and whether it resets.

v4 sweep_tier + de_minimis enumeration (added Phase D2 Commit 5). The Stage 2 payload includes a top-level provision_level_entities.by_type block. When a question concerns asset-sale proceeds:

1. SWEEP TIERS — when provision_level_entities.by_type.sweep_tier is present, enumerate every tier entry. Each tier carries attributes leverage_threshold (numeric), sweep_percentage (fraction; multiply by 100 for percent display), and section_reference. Sort by leverage_threshold descending. State each tier explicitly in the answer, e.g. 'At First Lien Leverage Ratio above 5.75x: 100% of Net Cash Proceeds swept [Definition of Applicable Net Cash Proceeds Percentage, clause (a)]; between 5.50x and 5.75x: 50%; at or below 5.50x: 0%.' Always cite the section_reference for each tier.

2. DE MINIMIS THRESHOLDS — when provision_level_entities.by_type.asset_sale_sweep is present, examine its attrs for de_minimis carveouts. Look for individual_de_minimis_usd, individual_de_minimis_pct, annual_de_minimis_usd, annual_de_minimis_pct, individual_uses_greater_of, annual_uses_greater_of, annual_permits_carryforward. Percentages are stored as fractions (0.15 = 15%; 0.30 = 30%). State both individual-transaction and annual carveouts explicitly with their dollar and percentage thresholds, e.g. 'Asset sales below de minimis thresholds are exempt from the sweep: individually, the greater of $20M or 15% of Consolidated EBITDA per transaction; in the aggregate, the greater of $40M or 30% of Consolidated EBITDA per fiscal year.' If a specific dollar attribute is absent (e.g. individual_de_minimis_usd is null), report only the populated half (e.g. just the percentage threshold) — do not invent a dollar floor.

3. SWEEP EXEMPTIONS — boolean flags on asset_sale_sweep (e.g. exempt_non_collateral, exempt_ordinary_course) capture carveouts beyond de minimis. List each true-flag carveout in the answer.

4. RETAINED PROCEEDS — when sweep tiers leave a portion unswept, those Net Cash Proceeds become Retained Asset Sale Proceeds and flow to the Cumulative Amount via the builder_source_retained_asset_sale_proceeds norm. Mention this only if the question asks where retained proceeds go.

v4 upstream carveouts (added Phase E commit 4). The Stage 2 payload's provision_level_entities.by_type.asset_sale_sweep also carries TWO carveout flag pairs that govern asset-sale permissibility upstream of the sweep tiers and de minimis (Phase E commit 2 / commit 3 added these):

5. PRODUCT-LINE / 2.10(c)(iv) EXEMPTION — when permits_product_line_exemption_2_10_c_iv is true, Section 2.10(c)(iv) (or analogous) provides a mandatory-prepayment exemption for proceeds from the sale of a product line, line of business, or substantially all of a product line, gated on a First Lien Leverage Ratio threshold (product_line_2_10_c_iv_threshold) OR a pro forma no-worse test. State this as a separate carveout from the leverage-tier sweep percentage (it operates upstream — proceeds that qualify never enter the sweep at all). When the threshold attribute is null, report only the existence of the carveout plus the no-worse-test branch.

6. SECTION 6.05(z) UNLIMITED BASKET — when permits_section_6_05_z_unlimited is true, Section 6.05(z) (or the highest-numbered clause of the asset sales covenant) provides an UNLIMITED disposition basket gated on a First Lien Leverage Ratio threshold (section_6_05_z_threshold) OR a pro forma no-worse test. Distinguish from the 2.10(c)(iv) exemption: 6.05(z) is permissive of the disposition itself (under the negative covenant), while 2.10(c)(iv) is a sweep-side exemption (under mandatory prepayment). They typically combine — proceeds from a 6.05(z) disposition may also qualify for the 2.10(c)(iv) sweep exemption if the leverage test is met.";

# Category M: Unrestricted Subsidiary Distributions
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "M";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check scalar answers about unrestricted subsidiary distribution mechanics, basket carve-outs for unsub dividends, and interaction with designation/re-designation rules. Note whether distributions from unsubs are subject to the general RP prohibition or have a categorical carve-out.";

# Category N: Dividend Capacity Calculation
# Phase D2 commit 3 — replaced with v4-aware content. The valence_v4 DB
# carries this v4 form; valence (v3) keeps its own copy via init_schema.py
# loading the original v3-era guidance. Future v3↔v4 sync should preserve
# the divergence: v3 reasons over capacity_category; v4 reasons over
# action_scope and capacity_composition.
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "N";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Category N covers dividend-capacity calculation under the v4 deontic-norm projection. Capacity-aggregation answers should reason over v4 norm attributes directly:

CAPACITY ATTRIBUTES PER NORM:
- cap_usd: fixed dollar cap (e.g. $130,000,000).
- cap_grower_pct: EBITDA-grower component, used as 'greater of cap_usd and cap_grower_pct% of Consolidated EBITDA'.
- action_scope: 'specific' | 'general' | 'reallocable'. 'reallocable' means the basket's unused capacity flows to other action types via cross-reference (e.g. an RDP basket's unused capacity reallocates to dividends under 6.06(j)).
- capacity_composition: 'fungible' | 'additive' | 'computed_from_sources' | 'unlimited_on_condition' | 'categorical' | 'n_a' | 'standalone'. Describes the geometry of capacity combination, not the inclusion rule.
- norm_kind: human-readable kind (e.g. 'general_rp_basket_permission', 'general_rdp_basket_permission'). Do NOT make inclusion decisions based on the substring 'rdp' or 'investment' in norm_kind — use action_scope.

INCLUSION RULES FOR AGGREGATE CAPACITY:
1. Every norm with action_scope: 'reallocable' contributes to the aggregate dividend capacity, regardless of which covenant it nominally serves. Sum these explicitly.
2. Norms with action_scope: 'specific' that have a numeric cap_usd or cap_grower_pct AND name a dividend-relevant action are listed separately as restricted-purpose capacity (e.g. management_equity_basket_permission for officer/director repurchases).
3. Norms with capacity_composition: 'computed_from_sources' (e.g. builder_usage_permission) have their fixed floor in the starter source (look up the contributing builder_source_starter norm via norm_contributes_to_capacity edges).
4. Norms with capacity_composition: 'unlimited_on_condition' (e.g. ratio_rp_basket_permission) provide unlimited capacity contingent on a condition; list separately, do not include in the dollar sum.
5. Norms with capacity_composition: 'categorical' or 'n_a' (e.g. tax_distribution_basket_permission, holdco_overhead_basket_permission, unrestricted_sub_equity_distribution_permission) are categorical permissions without a fixed dollar cap; list separately.
6. shares_capacity_pool edge between two reallocable norms means their caps are NOT additive (the same dollar funds either) — count only the larger cap, not the sum. Absence of shares_capacity_pool means independent pools that ARE summed.

ARITHMETIC FORMAT:
Show the per-norm contribution explicitly:
  norm_id [§section, p.page]: $cap_usd or cap_grower_pct% EBITDA
List the reallocable+aggregate baskets, then sum: $X + $Y + $Z = $TOTAL.
List restricted-purpose, unlimited-conditional, and categorical baskets separately, each with its own line and its own scope/condition.
Do NOT state a total without the per-norm breakdown.";

# Category P: Unsub Distribution Basket Carve-outs
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "P";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check scalar answers for unsub distribution basket carve-outs, including dollar caps, percentage limitations, and interaction with other RP baskets. Note whether the carve-out is a categorical permission or subject to conditions.";

# Category S: RDP General
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "S";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check scalar answers for subordinated debt payment restrictions, general prohibition scope, and interaction with restricted payment provisions. Note whether RDP restrictions apply to all junior debt or only specified subordinated indebtedness.";

# Category T: RDP Baskets
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "T";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check rdp_basket entities (refinancing, general, ratio, builder, equity-funded subtypes). Use capacity_category to classify. Note: RDP baskets use provision_has_rdp_basket relation, NOT provision_has_basket — these are a SEPARATE hierarchy from RP baskets.";

# Category Z: Pattern Detection
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "Z";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Cross-reference pattern flags on the provision entity (jcrew_pattern_detected, serta_pattern_detected, collateral_leakage_pattern_detected). These are computed boolean signals — state what patterns are present and what they indicate. Check entity data for the underlying facts that triggered each pattern flag.";


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# J.CREW CATEGORIES
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# JC1: Structural Analysis
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "JC1";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Structure analysis around blocker existence, scope, binding parties, and asset coverage. Check jcrew_blocker entity boolean attributes for coverage assessment — read the annotations to understand what each boolean means. Check lien_release_mechanics entity for automatic release triggers and their interaction with blocker provisions.";

# JC2: Definition Quality
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "JC2";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "For each key definition referenced by the blocker, check definition_clause entities. State whether each definition is inline, by cross-reference to another document, or absent. Focus on practical impact of definition gaps — e.g., if 'Material' is determined by the Borrower Agent in good faith with no objective threshold, the borrower controls what is considered material.";

# JC3: Interaction Patterns
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "JC3";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check investment_pathway entities for multi-hop chain analysis. For each pathway show: source and destination entity types, dollar and percentage caps, whether uncapped, and section references. Check basket_reallocation entities for cross-covenant capacity flows. Analyze how J.Crew blocker interacts with investment baskets, unrestricted subsidiary designation, and lien covenants. If the blocker binds ALL Restricted Subsidiaries, note this closes multi-hop chain pathways.";


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# MFN CATEGORIES
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# MFN1: Core Structure
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "MFN1";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check mfn_provision scalar answers for: existence, threshold in basis points, whether adjustment is automatic. The threshold is the single most important number — always state it explicitly. State whether comparison is all-in yield or margin-only.";

# MFN2: Facility & Debt Scope
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "MFN2";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "CRITICAL DISTINCTION — RATIO PRONG vs RATIO DEBT: When a question involves the ratio prong and MFN, ALWAYS distinguish between two separate concepts: (a) Debt incurred as a First Lien Incremental Term Facility under Section 2.19 using the ratio prong of the Incremental Cap (clause (I)) to SIZE the amount — this debt is still an Incremental Term Facility and is STILL SUBJECT to MFN conditions (u)-(z). The ratio prong determines HOW MUCH can be incurred, not WHETHER MFN applies. (b) Debt incurred OUTSIDE the agreement as Incremental Equivalent Debt or Ratio Debt under the debt incurrence covenant — this is categorically NOT subject to MFN because it is not a First Lien Incremental Term Facility. The exclusion_type='ratio' on mfn_exclusion entities may conflate these two concepts. When answering, always state WHICH incurrence vehicle is being used and whether the debt is inside or outside the agreement. Review each mfn_exclusion entity's exclusion_type attribute. Count total exclusions. Check excludes_from_mfn to identify which exclusions fully remove debt from MFN scope vs merely modify the calculation. Check can_stack_with_other_exclusions for stacking risk. Review mfn_freebie_basket entity for dollar_amount_usd and ebitda_pct — these represent quantifiable MFN-exempt capacity. Compute total exempt capacity from all sources. When answering about total MFN-free debt capacity, check CROSS-COVENANT ENTITIES for RP debt incurrence baskets. Debt incurred under the general debt basket (Section 6.01) or as Ratio Debt is not a First Lien Incremental Term Facility and is categorically not subject to MFN. SCENARIO ANALYSIS: When evaluating whether specific debt triggers MFN, check ALL mfn_exclusion entities before concluding. Read condition_logic on the provision (shown in the PROVISION header) — if 'conjunctive', ALL conditions must be met for MFN to apply. If ANY ONE condition fails, MFN does not apply. For each condition, use the applies_when attribute (the POSITIVE framing of when MFN applies). Check: does the debt described in the question satisfy applies_when? If NO for any condition, that condition fails and MFN does not apply. Lead your answer with the decisive condition — the one that resolves the question. Do not list 5 met conditions before revealing the 1 that fails. Boolean entity attributes and excludes_from_mfn values are definitive findings, not probabilistic. Do not hedge with 'likely' or 'potentially' when the data is clear.";

# MFN3: Yield Mechanics
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "MFN3";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check mfn_yield_definition entity's boolean attributes to determine yield coverage. More included components = stronger MFN. If both includes_oid and includes_floor_benefit are false, flag the yield exclusion pattern as a significant structural weakness. Check oid_amortization_method and comparison_baseline. Check differentiates_fixed_floating and yield_determination_authority for calculation methodology details. ALWAYS state the MFN threshold in basis points when discussing yield triggers. The threshold appears on the provision entity as threshold_bps — state it as a specific number (e.g., '75 basis points'), never as 'the threshold embedded in the provision.' When asked about which yield baseline is used for the MFN comparison (original vs current), check the yield dynamics attributes on the mfn_yield_definition entity: yield_recalculated_at_incurrence, reference_rate_changes_affect_yield, and market_price_affects_yield. These indicate whether the Effective Yield is static or dynamic and which components change over time. Do not assume the baseline is either the original closing yield or the current market yield without checking these attributes. The Effective Yield is a contractual calculation — read the entity data to determine what it includes and whether it changes.";

# MFN4: Sunset & Timing
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "MFN4";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check mfn_sunset_provision entity: sunset_exists, sunset_period_months, sunset_trigger_event. Short sunset without reset on refinancing = temporal weakness. Check sunset_resets_on_refi and sunset_tied_to_maturity. If sunset_timing_loophole is true, explain that the borrower can time debt issuance to just after sunset expiry.";

# MFN5: Governance & Waivers
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "MFN5";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Check scalar answers for sacred right status, amendment thresholds, agent discretion. Reference specific section numbers from entity section_reference attributes. State the specific consent threshold required to waive MFN.";

# MFN6: Loopholes & Weaknesses
match $cat isa ontology_category, has category_id "MFN6";
insert $cat has synthesis_guidance "Cross-reference ACROSS entity types: mfn_exclusion entities with excludes_from_mfn=true = structural gaps. mfn_yield_definition with both OID and floor excluded = yield exclusion pattern. mfn_sunset_provision with short sunset = temporal weakness. mfn_freebie_basket total capacity = quantifiable exempt amount. Count and characterize each loophole. Present total MFN-exempt capacity as a dollar figure when data supports it. For reclassification risk, check whether ratio/IED debt is excluded from MFN scope. When computing total MFN-exempt capacity, check the CROSS-COVENANT ENTITIES section for debt incurrence baskets from the RP provision. The general debt basket (general_investment_basket or general_rp_basket) provides capacity for debt that is NOT an Incremental Term Facility and therefore not subject to MFN. The ratio_basket entity has ratio_threshold showing the leverage test (e.g., 5.1x). Sum: freebie dollar_amount_usd + general basket basket_amount_usd + any EBITDA-based carveout. Present individual components AND total dollar figure.";
